### Gibbs sampler fit

I fit the model using the Gibbs sampler derived in Problem 1. To make posterior summaries interpretable, I addressed label switching by reordering the component means after each iteration so that (\mu\_1 \< \mu\_2), and relabeling cluster assignments accordingly.

```{r}
set.seed(731)

time_gibbs <- system.time({
  fit_gibbs <- gibbs_mixture(
    y = y,
    K = K,
    sigma2 = sigma2,
    n_iter = 10000,
    burn = 2000
  )
})

time_gibbs
fit_gibbs$mu_post_mean
```

### Variational Bayes fit

I also fit the model using coordinate ascent variational inference (CAVI), using the ELBO to monitor convergence.

```{r}
time_vb <- system.time({
  fit_vb <- vb_mixture(
    y = y,
    K = K,
    sigma2 = sigma2,
    max_iter = 1000,
    tol = 1e-8
  )
})

time_vb
fit_vb$m
```

