### Gibbs sampler diagnostics

To assess convergence, I ran three Gibbs chains with different initial values.

```{r}
set.seed(2026)

init1 <- sample(1:K, n, replace = TRUE)
init2 <- ifelse(y < median(y), 1, 2)
init3 <- ifelse(y < mean(y), 2, 1)

fit_gibbs_1 <- gibbs_mixture(y, K = K, sigma2 = sigma2, n_iter = 10000, burn = 2000, init_c = init1)
fit_gibbs_2 <- gibbs_mixture(y, K = K, sigma2 = sigma2, n_iter = 10000, burn = 2000, init_c = init2)
fit_gibbs_3 <- gibbs_mixture(y, K = K, sigma2 = sigma2, n_iter = 10000, burn = 2000, init_c = init3)
```

```{r}
trace_df <- bind_rows(
